    <note>Ru(1) He [23917] See documentation in 1148 jinshi list, wujia #82, for great grandson, Xiang [23923]. It is obvious that the Shengxian Ru(1) must be members of the same root lineage. Since He's grandson, Zhi [23922], held office w/o jinshi, he must have been related fairly closely to either or both Yue [23919] (jinshi in 1042) and Kai [23918] (jinshi in 1053). I am making Kai, Yue and He first cousins although Yue may represent a generation earlier. I am making Shaoting [23920], jinshi in 1145, a great grandnephew of He, Kui [23924] (who earned the jinshi in 1199 and has the same generational indicator as Xiang) as Zhi's son and Xiang's younger brother, and Yu [23925], who earned the degree in 1211, as Xiang's grandson. No kinship connections made in any of the sources for Shengxian jinshi, but earlier Shengxian jinshi are missing from the sources for prefectural jinshi.</note>
